  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Collinear Resonance Ionisation Spectroscopy (CRIS) experiment at CERN has achieved high-resolution resonance ionisation laser spectroscopy with a full width at half maximum linewidth of 20(1) MHz for <math altimg="si10.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><msup><mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>219</mn><mtext>,</mtext><mn>221</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></math> Fr, and has measured isotopes as short lived as 5 ms with <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><msup><mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>214</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></math> Fr. This development allows for greater precision in the study of hyperfine structures and isotope shifts, as well as a higher selectivity of single-isotope, even single-isomer, beams. These achievements are linked with the development of a new laser laboratory and new data-acquisition systems.</subfield>
